<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I was sitting around one day and thought to myself
<br />

<br />
"Self, what would it take to get your intelligence up to 355?"
<br />

<br />
I said, "You know what Self, I think I would like to find out."
<br />

<br />
this was also after i twinked my wizzard out to 255 int at level 2  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_dance.gif" alt="eusa_dance.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
so i started looking up gear, taking into consideration what would be available and what would not, etc
<br />

<br />
so here you go, my calculations for hitting 355 intelligence.  All the gear below is available if you are in the right situation.  This (as far as I can tell) is the quickest way to 355.  It may not be the most efficient way, but the numbers work, and the gear is damn good too.  Any enchanter would give his/her left/right <insert body part with both a right and a left here> to get some of this gear.
<br />

<br />
Basically this is a road map on how to max your intelligence.  But please keep in mind that this has no considerations for +CHA or any other stats for that matter.  I was focussing on +INT only.
<br />

<br />
so without further a'do.  Here you are, the Roadmap to a Smarter You
<br />
----------------------------------------------------
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>I wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
i did some calculations and the +int on:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=11298" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Bracer of Visions</a> = +13 x 2 = 26 (2 bracers per toon)
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=9836" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Circlet of Visions</a> = +20
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=13614" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Gloves of Visions</a> = +18
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=16931" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Pantaloons of Visions</a> = +23
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=32140" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Robe of Visions</a> = +30
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=11578" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Sleeves of Visions</a> = +20
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=20425" target="_blank" class="postlink">Romar's Slippers of Visions</a> = +20
<br />

<br />
All of the above is the Silk armor from PoTime.  With the new backflagging solution, this set of armor will be more common among Enchanters of Norrath
<br />

<br />
When I made my toon, his intelligence was at 143, so pretending that I have the AA's to raise my max intelligence up to 355, lets do some math.
<br />

<br />
143 (base) + 157 (total from Time Gear) = 300
<br />

<br />
okay so we're still 55 points away from an Uber Enchanter, lets continue
<br />

<br />
I assume that you would have your epic if you got this far, so lets add that in
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=10650" target="_blank" class="postlink">Staff of the Serpent</a> = +20
<br />

<br />
up to 320
<br />

<br />
There is also a pretty common drop called the Wand of Temporal Power.  It drops off of Vallon Zek in Time.  So this one is a pretty good bet as well.  Heck, if you're leading the raid, you may be able to just claim it.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=21876" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wand of Temporal Power</a> = +20
<br />

<br />
up to 340, only 15 more to go
<br />

<br />
now add in:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=11052" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tobrin's Mystical Eyepatch</a> +15
<br />

<br />
and BOOM!!!!
<br />

<br />
Intelligence at 355 </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
So there you go, flame it, use it, worship it, do whatever you want with it</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
